---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import BrandName from "../components/BrandName.astro";
import Seal from "../components/Seal.astro";
---
<Layout title="Tater Tot Index | About the Council">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <div class="font-display uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-xs text-rust mb-3">
        A Brief History
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold uppercase text-5xl sm:text-6xl letterpress">
        About the Council
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-lg text-brown-warm mt-4">
        On Frozen Potato Affairs &middot; Established 1953, Ontario, Oregon
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-center mb-12">
      <Seal size={140} year={1953} />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8 font-serif text-lg text-brown-deep leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        In the spring of 1953, in the small town of Ontario, Oregon &mdash; a place
        whose principal export had long been the russet potato &mdash; two brothers
        confronted a problem. The slivered scraps left over from the production of
        the frozen french fry were, by every conventional measure, waste.
      </p>
      <p>
        And yet, those slivered scraps were also the cleanest, most flavorful
        portion of the potato. Discarding them was, the brothers concluded, a
        moral failure. They were chopped, seasoned, formed into modest cylinders,
        and frozen. The result was, to the surprise of no one who has tasted one,
        magnificent.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Council on Frozen Potato Affairs was constituted shortly thereafter,
        chartered with a single purpose: to ensure that the American household
        understood the proper place of <BrandName /> in the modern economy &mdash; not
        merely as a side dish, but as the most reliable unit of value the
        domestic kitchen has ever produced.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold uppercase text-3xl pt-6 letterpress">
        Our Methodology
      </h2>
      <p>
        Each tot is standardized at 8.5 grams. Volume is computed at 10
        milliliters per tot, accounting for ordinary packing density. Prices are
        established by reference to the prevailing retail rate at the major
        American grocer:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-none pl-0 border-2 border-brown-deep bg-cream-light p-6 space-y-2">
        <li class="flex justify-between gap-4">
          <span class="font-serif">Name-Brand <BrandName />:</span>
          <span class="font-stat tabular text-rust-deep">$0.14 per ounce</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex justify-between gap-4 pt-2 border-t border-brown-deep/20">
          <span class="font-serif">Generic <BrandName /> (private label):</span>
          <span class="font-stat tabular text-rust-deep">$0.093 per ounce</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The two figures are not, in the Council's view, in competition. The
        name-brand figure represents the proper standard of quality and consistency
        the consumer has come to expect. The generic figure represents the
        prerogative of the thrifty household to obtain a comparable value at a
        modest discount. Both are accommodated in the Index by way of the brand
        toggle in the navigation bar above.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display font-bold uppercase text-3xl pt-6 letterpress">
        A Note on Substitution
      </h2>
      <p>
        The Council does not, in any official capacity, recommend that the citizen
        actually substitute tots for a residence, an automobile, or a marriage.
        The Index is intended as an aid to economic perspective, not a
        prescription. Consult a financial advisor &mdash; and, in matters of nutrition, a
        registered dietitian &mdash; before making any substantial life change on the
        basis of this publication.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 text-center">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-block bg-brown-deep text-cream-light px-8 py-4 font-display uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-sm hover:bg-rust-deep transition-colors border-2 border-brown-deep"
      >
        Return to the Index
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
